title: Australian lawyers working on case against Papua New Guinea PM Peter O'Neill barred from country
text:
Australian lawyers working on case ag... Australian lawyers working on case against Papua New Guinea PM Peter O'Neill barred from country Next Story Prev Story 5 hrs ago Read more: The Age 
Two Australian lawyers have been barred from entering Papua New Guinea, after preparing to represent authorities in a case against PNG Prime Minister Peter O'Neill, who has been served an arrest warrant for alleged official corruption. Queensland barrister Greg Egan and his junior counsel Terence Lambert, who are representing PNG fraud investigators, argue their travel ban is "a ploy" to further undermine the case against Mr O'Neill.   The Age.
